Description: Provides law firms, corporations, and Bar Associations with professional and entertaining, live and webcast, turn-key CLE programs.
Full Description: Since 1999, Internet For Lawyers has provided law firms, corporations, and local and state Bar Associations around the country with professional and entertaining turn-key, live and webcast Continuing Legal Education (CLE) programs. The company focuses on delivering information about free investigative, background, and legal research resources available on the Internet.   Its continuing legal education programs focus on teaching legal professionals how to use the Internet and technology to practice law and research more efficiently and cost effectively. For these courses, they have also developed comprehensive custom-written materials.   While they primarily offer all-day seminars, some Bar associations choose to market two separate half-day seminars to offer their members maximum flexibility.   Prior to founding Internet For Lawyers, company President Carole Levitt has more than 20 years of extensive and diversified experience in the legal field as an attorney, Internet trainer, law librarian, and as a law school faculty member. Since starting the company, she has presented hundreds of seminars teaching legal professionals the advantages of conducting investigative, legal, and business research via the Internet.   Internet For Lawyers clients also have the benefit of Vice President Mark Rosch's 20 years of traditional marketing experience. Prior to co-founding Internet For Lawyers, he was head of a major cable television network Public Relations department. In addition to co-presenting with Levitt, he manages Internet For Lawyers' web site.   Levitt and Rosch are co-authors of The Cybersleuth's Guide to the Internet (IFL Press, 2014), Google Gmail and Calendar in One Hour for Lawyers (ABA, 2013) Find Info Like a Pro, Volume 2: Mining the Internet's Public Records for Investigative Research (ABA, 2011), Find Info Like a Pro, Volume 1: Mining the Internet's Publicly Available Resources for Investigative Research (ABA, 2010), Google for Lawyers: Essential Search Tips and Productivity Tools (ABA, 2010), and The Lawyer's Guide to Fact Finding on the Internet (ABA, 2003 & 2006) and numerous other magazine articles. Separately, Levitt has co-authored Internet Legal Research on a Budget (ABA, 2014) with Judy K. Davis.   The Internet For Lawyers Internet Investigative Research Update blog (http://www.netforlawyers.com/blog) keeps readers up to date with the latest free and low-cost investigative and background research resources freely available on the Internet.
